# Keep AGENTS.md up to date

AGENTS.md is the project's readme for AI agents. When you change any of the following, update AGENTS.md so future agents have correct context:

- **Scripts and config** — New or changed npm scripts, Vite/SvelteKit/Tauri config, build outputs, or ports
- **Project structure** — New top-level dirs, moving code between `src/` and `src-tauri/`, or new important paths
- **Conventions** — Format/lint/test commands, naming, or "do not edit" files (e.g. `src/bindings.ts`)
- **Env and secrets** — New env vars, `.env*` usage, or credential handling
- **Stack and deps** — New frameworks, UI libs, or Rust crates that affect how to run or build
- **Data sources** — Adding, removing, or changing a data source (GitHub, Google, local git, JIRA, Zulip, etc.), its auth method, or its API

Edit the relevant section(s) in AGENTS.md; keep the same structure and level of detail so the file stays scannable and accurate.
